event.accessToken.title: EventAccessToken

descriptions: Information about the Client used during this token exchange.
event.client.title: EventClient

descriptions: The client id of the application the user is logging in to.
event.client.client_id.title: EventClientClient_id

descriptions: An object for holding other application properties.
event.client.metadata.title: EventClientMetadata

descriptions: The name of the application (as defined in the Dashboard).
event.client.name.title: EventClientName

descriptions: Details about the Organization associated with the current transaction.
event.organization.title: EventOrganization

descriptions: The friendly name of the Organization.
event.organization.display_name.title: EventOrganizationDisplay_name

descriptions: The Organization identifier.
event.organization.id.title: EventOrganizationId

descriptions: Metadata associated with the Organization.
event.organization.metadata.title: EventOrganizationMetadata

descriptions: The name of the Organization.
event.organization.name.title: EventOrganizationName

descriptions: Details about the request that initiated the transaction.
event.request.title: EventRequest

descriptions:
The body of the POST request. This data will only be available
              during refresh token, Client Credential Exchange flows and
              PreUserRegistration Action.
event.request.body.title: EventRequestBody

descriptions:
The hostname that is being used for the authentication
              flow.
event.request.hostname.title: EventRequestHostname

descriptions: The originating IP address of the request.
event.request.ip.title: EventRequestIp

descriptions: The language requested by the browser.
event.request.language.title: EventRequestLanguage

descriptions: The HTTP method used for the request
event.request.method.title: EventRequestMethod

descriptions:
The value of the User-Agent header received when
              initiating the transaction.
event.request.user_agent.title: EventRequestUser_agent

descriptions: Information about the Resource Server that is issuing the access token.
event.resource_server.title: EventResource_server

descriptions:
The identifier of the resource server. For example:
              https://your-api.example.com.
event.resource_server.identifier.title: EventResource_serverIdentifier

descriptions: Information about the Tenant used during this token exchange.
event.tenant.title: EventTenant

descriptions: The name of the tenant.
event.tenant.id.title: EventTenantId

descriptions: Information about the Credentials Exchange transaction.
event.transaction.title: EventTransaction

descriptions:
The scopes specified (if any) when requesting the access
              token.
event.transaction.requested_scopes.title: EventTransactionRequested_scopes
